oracle.pg.rdbms

Interface OraclePgqlResult

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    OraclePgqlResultImpl

    public interface OraclePgqlResult
    Holds a single row in a PGQL query result.

    • Method Detail

      • getColumnType

        OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type getColumnType(int elementIdx)
        Gets the column type for the result element at given position. The first element is at position 1.

        Possible values are:

        OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type.VERTEX
        OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type.EDGE
        OraclePgqlColumnDescriptor.Type.VALUE

        Parameters:
        elementIdx - the result element position
        Returns:
        the column type

      • getEdge

        OracleEdge getEdge(int elementIdx)
            throws OraclePropertyGraphException
        Gets the Edge object for the result element at given position. The first element is at position 1.
        Parameters:
        elementIdx - the result element position
        Returns:
        the OracleEdge oject for this result element
        Throws:
        OraclePropertyGraphException

      • getResultElements

        the result elements for this result row

      • getValue

        java.lang.Object getValue(int elementIdx)
                   throws OraclePropertyGraphException
        Gets the value for the result element at given position. The first element is at position 1.
        Parameters:
        elementIdx - the result element position
        Returns:
        the result element value
        Throws:
        OraclePropertyGraphException

      • getValueType

        int getValueType(int elementIdx)
        Gets the value type for the result element at given position. -1 is returned for VERTEX and EDGE result elements. The first element is at position 1.

        Value types correspond to values in the T column of the property graph relational schema.

        Parameters:
        elementIdx - the result element position
        Returns:
        the value type

      • getVertex

        OracleVertex getVertex(int elementIdx)
                throws OraclePropertyGraphException
        Gets the Vertex object for the result element at given position. The first element is at position 1.
        Parameters:
        elementIdx - the result element position
        Returns:
        the OracleVertex object for this result element
        Throws:
        OraclePropertyGraphException
